Title: Nahm's equations, $N=1^*$ domain walls, and D-strings in $AdS_5 x S_5$
Authors: C. Bachas, J. Hoppe and B. Pioline
Comments: Latex, 26 pages, 3 figures, uses JHEP.cls; v4: discussion of
  holographic interpretation of `fuzzy D-string' configurations modified. Minor
  esthetic changes otherwise
Report-no: HUTP-00/A025, LPTENS-00-30, LPTHE-00-29
Journal-ref: JHEP 0107 (2001) 041
\\
  We consider the following two problems: classical domain walls in the $N=1^*$
mass deformation of the maximally supersymmetric Yang Mills theory, and
D-strings as external magnetic sources in the context of the AdS/CFT
correspondence. We show that they are both described by Nahm's equations with
unconventional boundary conditions, and analyze the relevant moduli space of
solutions. We argue that general `fuzzy sphere' configurations of D-strings in
AdS$_5$ correspond to Wilson-'t Hooft lines in higher representations of the
dual SU(n) gauge theory.
